<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101933701991068></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101933701991068><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101933701991068>RE: mend and bind wound</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101933701991068#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>539 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Apr 20th 5:10 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Bind Wound and Mend have nothing to do with each other.&nbsp;&nbsp;Your mend skill is your percentage chance for success.  At 29, you will succeed 29% of the time.  At 100 mend never fails.  It always gives you back 25% of your hitpoint total (including buffs) and is on a 6 minute timer.  Skill above 100 offers no added benefit.<br><br>Safefall increase:  Go to a zone wall that's fairly steep.  EC/WC, OT and many others work well.  Run all the way up the wall till it won't let you go further.  Face outward, switch to a third person view, and run down.  Count the number of 'falling' animations you see.  If you see 4 or more, you've got a good spot.  If you see less, try a different area of the wall (different slope).  Now just go forward and backward repeatedly.  You get a skill check every time you see the falling animation.<br><br>Another way - one I never tried - is to use the teleporters inside the Erudin zone.  Reportedly, you can arrange it so that you run off the balcony/wall and straight onto the teleporter pad that puts you back up to the top of the balcony/wall.  Just hit auto run and sit back.  But - don't go AFK - GM's take a dim view of AFK skill training.<br><br>The best jewelry you can get is a pair of 6/65 rings.  You might swing those for 1k.  You'll wear them to your 50s and beyond.  After that, try to get a pair of Black Sapphire Electrum earrings (ac2 hp35).  Those 4 pieces will get you 200 hp - incredible for a 12 monk, and will last you till your 50s.<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Strange Brew - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
